article.description: UC Santa Barbara dominates Hawaii Pacific 76-50
article.headline: UC Santa Barbara dominates Hawaii Pacific 76-50
article.linkText: UC Santa Barbara dominates Hawaii Pacific 76-50
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Alan Williams had 27 points and 17 rebounds as UC Santa Barbara coasted to a 76-50 victory over Hawaii Pacific Friday. Williams was 10 of 15 from the field and was good on 7 of 12 free throws. Michael Bryson, 13 points, and Kyle Boswell, 10 points, were also in double digits for UC Santa Barbara. Hawaii Pacific led 6-1 on 3-point jumpers by Malte Zeigenhagen and Darry Jones Jr., but the Gauchos quickly took the lead 8-6 on a Kyle Boswell steal that led to a Williams' jump shot with 17:37 remaining in the first half. The UC Santa Barbara defense stymied Hawaii Pacific, holding the Sea Warriors scoreless for more than 6 minutes in the first period to take a 16-9 lead. They were ahead 34-20 at the half. Ziegenhagen led the Sea Warriors with 14 points. Justin Long contributed 12 points.
